tasks.description:
Phase 2 Steps 6-7: Unify edit paths. Add a single applyEdit(mutation, options?) in useTimelineCommit.ts accepting a discriminated union:

```typescript
type TimelineEditMutation = 
  | { type: 'rows'; rows: TimelineRow[]; metaUpdates?: Record<string, Partial<ClipMeta>>; metaDeletes?: string[]; clipOrderOverride?: ClipOrderMap }
  | { type: 'config'; resolvedConfig: ResolvedConfig };

type ApplyEditOptions = {
  save?: boolean;
  selectedClipId?: string | null;
  selectedTrackId?: string | null;
  transactionId?: string;
  semantic?: boolean;
};
```

Migrate ALL internal hook callers:
- useClipEditing.ts — multiple applyTimelineEdit calls + applyResolvedConfigEdit in handleSelectedClipChange
- useClipDrag.ts — applyTimelineEdit at drag end
- useClipResize.ts — applyTimelineEdit at resize end
- useExternalDrop.ts — applyTimelineEdit at drop
- useTimelineTrackManagement.ts — applyTimelineEdit in moveClipToRow, applyResolvedConfigEdit in createTrackAndMoveClip and handleTrackPopoverChange
- useAssetManagement.ts — applyTimelineEdit calls

CRITICAL: createTrackAndMoveClip uses type:'config' path preserving existing no-overlap-resolution semantics (new track = no neighbors).

Update TimelineEditorContextValue in useTimelineState.types.ts to expose applyEdit replacing applyTimelineEdit. Update UseTimelineDataResult interface. Remove old wrappers once all callers migrated.

Run tests after each file migration. Run full suite + tsc --noEmit at end.

Phase 5 Step 12: Simplify useDerivedTimeline signature caching. With Phase 1's default-reject poll model in place, assess whether the configSignatureRef/stableResolvedConfigRef mechanism (lines 19-35) can be simplified.

IMPORTANT: The repo enforces react-hooks/exhaustive-deps as error. Do NOT use useMemo(() => data?.resolvedConfig, [data?.signature]) — this violates the lint rule. Instead, keep [data] as the dependency and compare signature internally (matching the current pattern), or use a simpler ref-based approach:
```typescript
const resolvedConfig = useMemo(() => {
  if (!data) return null;
  // signature comparison happens naturally since data reference
  // only changes when poll is accepted (which requires signature diff)
  return data.resolvedConfig;
}, [data]);
```

If Remotion preview flickers after simplification: REVERT and keep current ref-based cache with clarifying comment.

The hook computes 7 derived values and is called twice — preserve all of it. Only the signature stabilization mechanism is the simplification target.

Run tests.
